Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine pink-buff. Rectangular stamp with 8-ray star symbol.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 163, 9. Name Xenophanes. Close to the die of Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, MGR 1120.36.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0869)
